singular definition: of or relating to a separate person or thing.

SINGULAR, an open source Computer Algebra System (CAS) - SINGULAR (typeset Singular) is a computer algebra system for polynomial computations with special emphasis on the needs of commutative algebra, algebraic geometry, and singularity theory.
Singular number, in grammar, a term for words denoting a unit quantity, as opposed to the plural and other forms
Singular measure, a measure or probability distribution whose support has zero Lebesgue (or other) measure
